  "body": "Summary\n- Add scripts/flakecheck: a Go tool that parses modified *_test.go files, enumerates test selectors (including subtests) via go/ast, and runs each selector N times with `go test -json` to detect flakes.\n- Default repeat count is 10; DB-friendly defaults: `-p 4 -parallel 4`.\n- Output is suppressed for stable tests; prints only flaky or broken selectors with fail counts. Exits non-zero on any flake or broken test.\n- Makefile: add `test-flakes` target which depends on `test-postgres-docker` and runs the tool.\n- CI: add `go-tests` path filter and `test-go-flakes` job (Linux) that runs for PRs with changed *_test.go files. The job appends the flake summary to the GitHub Actions step summary.\n\nImplementation notes\n- AST scanning mirrors existing patterns (see `scripts/typegen`).\n- Subtests are collected from literal-named `t.Run` chains; dynamic names aren\u2019t supported.\n- Uses `-count=1` and anchors per-level run regex (e.g., `^TestFoo$/^case$`).\n\nTesting\n- Built and ran locally with no modified tests (no-op). CI job leverages existing Postgres bootstrap.\n\nFollow-ups (optional)\n- Add JSON/JUnit outputs for deeper analysis.\n- Optional PR comment bot integration.",
